DDL (Data Definition Language) 
------------------------------
-These commands are given to manage database objects such as tables, views etc. 
Example: 
        1.CREATE 
        2.ALTER 
        3.RENAME
        4.DROP 
        5.TRUNCATE 

1.CREATE TABLE
--------------
Syntax:
      CREATE TABLE table_name ( 
             column1 datatype(size), 
             column2 datatype(size), ……..
      );  

Example:
-Table Name: students
Sql-
    CREATE TABLE  students( 
           rollnumber int, 
           firstname varchar(30), 
           lastname varchar(30) 
    );  

| [Column Name] | [Data Type] | [Size] |
|  roll_number |    int      |  10    |
|  firstname   |  varchar    |  30    |
|  lastname    |  varchar    |  30    |

Show Table Structure
-------------------
Syntax:
      DESC table_name; 
Example:
      DESC students;

List All Tables
---------------
Sql- show tables;  

2.ALTER(Modifying Table)
-----------------------
-ALTER command is used to modify table structure.
-We can use ADD, CHANGE and RENAME option with ALTER command.

Add New Column
--------------
Syntax:
      ALTER TABLE table_name ADD column_name datatype(size);  
Example:
      ALTER TABLE students ADD address varchar(100);
      DESC students;

| [Column Name] | [Data Type]    | [Null] | [Default] |
|  rollnumber   | int            |  YES   |   NULL    |
|  firstname    | varchar(30)    |  YES   |   NULL    |
|  lastname     | varchar(30)    |  YES   |   NULL    |
|  address      | varchar(100)   |  YES   |   NULL    |

Note: 
-----
-By default, when using the ALTER TABLE statement to add a new column to a table, the column is added at the end of the existing column list.
-To add new column at the beginning.
Sql-  
    ALTER TABLE students ADD id int(10) FIRST;
-To add a new column at a specific position within the table, use the AFTER keyword followed by the name of the existing column.
Sql-
    ALTER TABLE students ADD age int(3) AFTER lastname;

CHANGE (Modifying Existing Column)
---------------------------------
-We can change name, data type and size of the column.
Syntax:
      ALTER TABLE employee CHANGE old_column_name  new_column_name datatype(size); 
Example:
      ALTER TABLE students CHANGE mark marks decimal(5,2);  

DROP (Delete Existing Columns)
------------------------------
Syntax:
      ALTER TABLE table_name DROP column_name;
Example:
      ALTER TABLE students DROP age; 

MODIFY (Alter with Modify Command)
----------------------------------
-MODIFY is used to change only the data type, size, or constraints of an existing column.
-Does'n change column name.
Syntax:
      ALTER TABLE table_name MODIFY  col_name datatype(size);
      ALTER TABLE table_name MODIFY  col_name1 datatype(size) AFTER col_name2;
Example:
      ALTER TABLE students MODIFY address varchar(50);

3.RENAME Table 
------------
Syntax:
RENAME TABLE old_table_name TO new_table_name; 
Example:
RENAME TABLE students TO students_backup; 

4.DROP(Delete Table)
--------------------
Syntax:
      DROP TABLE table_name;
Example
      DROP TABLE students; 

5.TRUNCATE(Deleting All Rows from Table )
---------------------------------------
Syntax:
TRUNCATE TABLE table_name;
Example:
TRUNCATE TABLE table_name;






























